{{Chinese|title=Quanguo Waiyu Shuiping Kaoshi|s=全国外语水平考试|t=全國外語水平考試|p=Quánguó Wàiyǔ Shuǐpíng Kǎoshì}}
'''''Quanguo Waiyu Shuiping Kaoshi''''' ("National Foreign Language Proficiency Test," '''WSK''') is a series of foreign language tests administered in [[Mainland China]] for educators who did not major in foreign languages.<ref name=RuanLeungp113>Ruan, Jiening and Cynthia Leung. ''Perspectives on Teaching and Learning English Literacy in China'' (Volume 3 of Multilingual Education). [[Springer Science & Business Media]], November 29, 2012. {{ISBN|9400749945}}, 9789400749948. p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=ZY5EAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA113 113].</ref> The [[National Education Examinations Authority]] (NEEA) of China developed these tests. Performance on the WSK determines whether one is permitted to take training, studies,<ref>Liu, Qingsi (The National Education Examinations Authority). "The National Education Examinations Authority and its English Language Tests." In: Cheng, Liying and Andy Curtis. ''English Language Assessment and the Chinese Learner''. [[Routledge]], March 17, 2010. {{ISBN|1135213879}}, 9781135213879. Start: [https://books.google.com/books?id=PX6MAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA29 29]. CITED: p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=PX6MAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA43 43].</ref> or additional studies within one's major in institutions outside of China.<ref name=RuanLeungp113/>

Some universities make successful completion of the WSK as a requirement for promotion in one's academic title.<ref name=RuanLeungp113/>

The [[Public English Test System]] (PETS) is the [[English as a second language|test for the English language]], available in five levels: PETS-1 through PETS-5.<ref>"[http://sk.neea.edu.cn/yydjks/show_sort_3.jsp?class_id=26_12_09 English]." Public English Test System. Retrieved on March 13, 2015.</ref> The other versions are '''TNF''' for the French language, '''NTD''' for the German language, '''NNS''' (日本語能力試験 ''Nihongo Nōryoku Shiken''; {{zh|first=s|s=日语水平考试|p=Rìyǔ Shuǐpíng Kǎoshì|labels=no}}<ref>"[http://sk.neea.edu.cn/infor.jsp?infoid=36195&class_id=26_13_04 日语水平考试（NNS）样卷]." ''Quanguo Waiyu Shuiping Kaoshi''. Retrieved on March 22, 2015.</ref><!--Kanji would be 日本語能力試験-->) for the Japanese language, and '''ТПРЯ''' ({{lang-ru|Тест по проверке уровня владения русским языком}} "Russian Language Proficiency Test"; {{zh|first=s|s=俄语水平考试|p=Éyǔ Shuǐpíng Kǎoshì|labels=no}}<ref>"[http://sk.neea.edu.cn/infor.jsp?infoid=36193 俄语水平考试（ТПРЯ）样卷]" ( {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6XDgEv2Aw?url=http://sk.neea.edu.cn/infor.jsp?infoid=36193 |date=2015-03-22 }}). ''Quanguo Waiyu Shuiping Kaoshi''. Retrieved on March 22, 2015.</ref>) for the Russian language.<ref>"[http://sk.neea.edu.cn/wyspks/ 首页] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150312214853/http://sk.neea.edu.cn/wyspks/ |date=2015-03-12 }}." Quanguo Waiyu Shuiping Kaoshi. Retrieved on March 13, 2015. "全国外语水平考试（ＷＳＫ）是为了鉴定非外语专业人员的外语水平而设置的考试，其成绩主要用于选拔国家公派出国留学人员。全国外语水平考试设英语（PETS-5）、法语(TNF)、德语(NTD)、日语(NNS)和俄语(ТПРЯ)五个语种。"</ref>

